title.narrative: Young people (girls and boys) have access to services and opportunities focusing on them.

description.narrative: UNICEF Jordan worked to reprioritize and reinforce its efforts to adapt to the new COVID-19 reality, in order to support the evolving needs of young people across Jordan. UNICEF worked directly with youth through qualitative and quantitative research, in order to strategically position interventions to benefit targeted populations, including young women and young people living in remote areas. Innovative and diverse interventions broadened young people’s access to training and continued learning, with evidence-based connections to opportunities in the labour market. These interventions reached 154,482;adolescents and youth (57 per centfemale). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
